#!N 
#!N  #!Rtall399 Vector interactors #!N The  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Set Attributes... 
#!EF dialog box for vector interactors has an additional field,  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
Selected Component #!EF , included at the top of the box. 
You can use this field to set different attributes for the 
different components of a vector. Do this by changing the component 
number with the stepper, and setting the attributes desired for that 
component. Repeat this process for all components of the vector. #!N 
#!N To assign common attributes to all components of a vector 
interactor, set the option box at the top of the dialog 
box to  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   All Components #!EF . When you do this, 
the component stepper is disabled, and any attributes you set are 
applied to all components of the vector. #!N #!N #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   
